## Problem

`cc-browser snapshot` returns 0 interactive elements on the LinkedIn feed page (`/feed/`). This means no buttons, links, or inputs can be found or clicked via the extension on that page. Screenshots via the extension also fail with "image readback failed".

Other LinkedIn pages (profiles, individual posts) work correctly.

## Root Cause

The `isVisible()` function in `tools/cc-browser/extension/content.js` (line 230-241) incorrectly marks elements as invisible when `el.offsetParent` is `null`. On the LinkedIn feed page, a top-level container element has `offsetParent === null` (likely due to CSS `contain`, `display: contents`, or a similar layout property). This causes `walk()` to skip that element and all its children, resulting in 0 captured elements.

```javascript
// Current code (line 230-241)
function isVisible(el) {
    if (!el.offsetParent && el.tagName !== 'BODY' && el.tagName !== 'HTML') {
      const style = getComputedStyle(el);
      if (style.display === 'none' || style.visibility === 'hidden') return false;
      if (style.position !== 'fixed' && style.position !== 'sticky') return false;  // <-- THIS rejects the feed container
    }
    const style = getComputedStyle(el);
    if (style.display === 'none' || style.visibility === 'hidden') return false;
    if (parseFloat(style.opacity) === 0) return false;
    return true;
}
```

## How to Fix

Remove the `offsetParent` check. Rely only on `getComputedStyle` checks which are the reliable visibility indicators:

```javascript
function isVisible(el) {
    const style = getComputedStyle(el);
    if (style.display === 'none' || style.visibility === 'hidden') return false;
    if (parseFloat(style.opacity) === 0) return false;
    if (el.offsetWidth === 0 && el.offsetHeight === 0 && style.overflow === 'hidden') return false;
    return true;
}
```

## How to Test

1. Deploy updated `content.js` to extension directory
2. Clear service worker cache: `rm -rf "$LOCALAPPDATA/cc-director/connections/linkedin/Default/Service Worker/"`
3. Close and reopen LinkedIn connection
4. Navigate to `https://www.linkedin.com/feed/`
5. Run `cc-browser --connection linkedin snapshot --compact` -- should return interactive elements
6. Verify profile pages and post pages still work (no regression)

## Impact

This blocks the LinkedIn Post workflow. The post composer opens on the feed page, and without snapshot/click working, we cannot click the Post button to submit posts.

## Files

- `tools/cc-browser/extension/content.js` -- `isVisible()` function at line 230
- Deploy to `%LOCALAPPDATA%/cc-director/bin/_cc-browser/extension/content.js`
